  "notes": "Running Cross Chasse\nInstead of closing feet above, keep moving ('running') forward:\nLeader\nS: RF fwd, CBMP, OP | FDW | HT\nS: LF fwd | FDW | T | -- | Sway(S) | CBM | Rise e/o 1\nQ: RF diagonally fwd | FDW | T | -- | Sway(L) | up\nQ: LF fwd, L shoulder leading | FDW | TH | -- | Sway(L) | up, lower e/o 3\nS: RF fwd in CBMP, OP | FDW | H | -- | Sway(S) | CBM | --\nFollower\nS: LF back, CBMP | BDW | TH \nPay attention not to do a lot rotation through shoulders.\nS: RF back | BDW | T | -- | Sway(S) | CBM | Rise e/o 1, NFR \nR shoulder connects down. \nQ: LF diagonally back | BDW | T | -- | Sway(R) | up\nDo not rotate L shoulder.\nStretch L side.\nQ: RF back, R shoulder leading | BDW | TH | -- | Sway(R) | up\nlower e/o 3\nS: LF back in CBMP | BDW | T | -- | Sway(S) | CBM | --",
